SCIENTIFIC_NAME: Pranesus eendrachtensis (Quoy & Gaimard, 1825) [regarded here as an unjustified emmendation; the species named for the presumed type locality, usually spelled T'Landt van d'Eendracht or Eendrachtsland (the name initially given to the area around Shark Bay by Dirk Hartog) and some argue that the name should probably have been spelled eendrachtensis, however Quoy & Gaimard clearly spelled the locality as d'Endracht and based on prevailing usage, the name endrachtensis should be retained]
